In terms of route of administration, the preference for intranasal delivery is on the rise due to its localized action and reduced systemic side effects compared to oral medications. Injectable routes, particularly for biologic therapies, are witnessing increasing adoption owing to their targeted approach and potential for improved treatment outcomes. The convenience offered by online pharmacies is driving their popularity among patients seeking easy access to medications, thereby reshaping traditional distribution channels in the nasal polyps treatment market.

